- An active workforce refers to employees who are currently working and have not retired or been terminated; 
- Average salary represents the total new salary divided by the number of employees in a specific job title; 
- Job titles with fewer than five active employees are excluded from the results.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(employee_id) AS employee_count
FROM employees
WHERE degree_id = (SELECT degree_id FROM degrees WHERE degree_name = 'Bachelor of Science in Computer Science');
